  <abstract>This citation accompanied the Distinguished Service Cross medal awarded to Pvt. John M. Sullivan, Co. H, 28th Inf. Regt., 1st Div. "for extraordinary heroism at the Meuse River, France." Sullivan served as a runner for HQ Co. and recounted going "over the top" so many times that he lost count. The DSC was awarded to men for extraordinary heroism. Italy's King Victor Emanuel III awarded Sullivan the Croce di Guerra (War Cross) for an act of bravery in No Man's Land.</abstract>
